five lakes supply water to mumbai lakes vihar vaitarna powai tulsi and tansa  tulsi lake   vihar lake  and  powai lake  are located within the metropolitan limits the first two being located within the  borivali national park  and supply part of the citys drinking water mumbai also has three small rivers within the city limits originating in the national park the coastline of the city is indented with numerous  creeks  and bays the eastern coast of salsette island is covered with large  mangrove   swamps  rich in  biodiversity  the western coast is mostly sandy and rocky
